data.description:
Located in tax-friendly West Gardiner, this custom build is under way. This 3 bedroom 2 bath executive style ranch/rambler with attached 2 car heated garage will appeal to most. The home is being built to be ''Age in Place'' ready with wide doorways and a wider than typical hallway. The heart of the home is the common great room, kitchen and dining area, which provides exceptional openness for visual interaction. The spacious kitchen will feature custom built cabinetry and will have a 8' kitchen island with butcher block top. The laundry is located just outside of the sleeping area and is convenient to both bathrooms. The office/third bedroom is convenient to the front porch entry. The master ''en-suite'' is situated in the rear of the home for plenty of privacy. The window and doors will have clean simple lines with custom trims. The 6'x24' covered front porch gives the home some wonderful curb appeal.  The nook located off from the dining area is an excellent location for a small office area, slide the custom barn door closed with your work from home day is complete! The on demand radiant propane heat and hot water along with LED lighting makes this home super efficient. A dual head heat pump only adds to the efficiency of this custom build package. The location is ideal, a slightly elevated building site, near the end of the road in Phase II of the Cold Creek Subdivision (nearly sold out). A great country location  just minutes from the vibrant downtown of Gardiner which boasts several restaurants, pubs, the completely renovated ''Johnson Hall'' custom meat market as well as banks and grocery stores. The waterfront on the Kennebec River always has happenings going on including free Friday night concerts during the summer and fall and several festivals each year. 
Please note: completed home will be slightly different from the attached plans. Utility room has been moved and garage doors are on the gable end.
